    "body": "Cherry-picks the same fix as #10198 (which targets `release/3.7.x`) into `rel/3.7`.\n\nUpstream commit: triton-lang/triton@5522c90a6e707ba0fe787590f2b89b8d62d4ec03\n\n## Original PR description\n\n> This allows sinking allocs back into the loop in case it is still possible. This does the reverse of alloc hoisting but it is okay since it is done after pipelining.\n\nNo conflicts; clean cherry-pick. 3 files changed, 215 insertions(+), 19 deletions(-).",
